Package: geex
Type: Package
Title: A Framework for Estimating Equations
Version: 0.2.2
Authors@R: c(person("Bradley", "Saul", role = c("aut", "cre"),
                    email = "bradleysaul@gmail.com"),
             person("Brian", "Barkley", role = c("ctb")))
Author: Bradley Saul [aut, cre], Brian Barkley [ctb]
Maintainer: Bradley Saul <bradleysaul@gmail.com>
Description: Provides a framework for estimating parameters from a set of unbiased
    estimating equations. Computes large sample variance using M-estimation
    theory as detailed by L.A. Stefanski and D.D. Boos in "The Calculus of M-
    estimation" (The American Statistician (2002), 56(1), 29-38). Also provides an 
    API to compute finite-sample variance corrections.
Depends:
    R (>= 3.1)
Imports:
    Matrix (>= 1.2-6),
    rootSolve (>= 1.6.6),
    numDeriv (>= 2014.2-1),
    lme4 (>= 1.1-12)
Suggests:
    testthat,
    knitr,
    dplyr,
    moments,
    sandwich,
    inferference,
    xtable
License: GPL (>= 2)
LazyData: TRUE
VignetteBuilder: knitr
RoxygenNote: 6.0.1
